      <context>
         <fig id="fig_izb_jzy_5gc">
            <image href="media/image817.png" id="image_lzb_jzy_5gc" placement="inline"/>
         </fig>
         <p>Typical Example</p>
         <p>Park the lift truck level, with the forks lowered and the mast tilted forward until the fork
      tips touch the floor.</p>
         <p>Block the drive wheels when parking on an incline.</p>
      </context>
      <ol>
         <li>
            <p>Park in authorised area only. Do not block traffic.<image href="media/image819.png" placement="inline"/>
            </p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Place the transmission controls in NEUTRAL.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Engage the parking brake (push the parking brake button). </p>
            <p>
               <fig>
                  <image href="media/image799(1).png" placement="inline"/>
               </fig>
               <p>Typical Example</p>
            </p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Lower the forks to the ground.  </p>
            <p>
               <note type="warning">
                  <p>Blocking the wheels will prevent unexpected lift truck movement, which could cause
            personal injury.</p>
               </note>
               <note type="note">
                  <p>Always run the engine at low idle for 5 minutes before turning off the engine.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Turn the ignition key switch to the OFF position and remove the key.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Actuate each loading lever several times to remove the residual pressure in the respective
        cylinders and hoses.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Block the drive wheels if parking on an incline.</p>
         </li>
      </ol>
